scala> "scala".take(3)
res0: String = sca

scala> "scala".drop(3)
res1: String = la

scala> "scala".take(10)
res2: String = scala

scala> "scala".drop(10)
res3: String = ""

scala> "scala".takeRight(3)
res4: String = ala

scala> "scala".dropRight(3)
res5: String = sc

These functions are easier to use as they return the whole string/an empty string instead of throwing an IndexOutOfBoundsException. They also require less index arithmetics.

